theme_ruta <- function(){ 
    font <- "Arial"   #assign font family up front
    
    theme_bw() %+replace%    #replace elements we want to change
    
    theme(
      axis.title = element_text(             #axis titles
                   family = font,            #font family
                   size = 8),               #font size
      
      axis.text = element_text(              #axis text
                   family = font,            #axis famuly
                   size = 8),                #font size,
      
      #grid elements
      panel.border= element_blank())+theme(plot.background = element_blank(),
        legend.position="none",
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        axis.line.y = element_line(size = 0.5), 
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 20,size=8, family="Arial", face = "italic", color = "black"),axis.text.y = element_text(family="Arial", face="plain", color="black", size=8, angle=0))
 
}
theme_ruta_ephys <- function(){ 
    font <- "Arial"   #assign font family up front
    
    theme_bw() %+replace%    #replace elements we want to change
    
    theme(
      axis.title = element_text(             #axis titles
                   family = font,            #font family
                   size = 8),               #font size
      
      axis.text = element_text(              #axis text
                   family = font,            #axis famuly
                   size = 8),                #font size,
      
      #grid elements
      panel.border= element_blank())+theme(plot.background = element_blank(),
        legend.position="none",
        axis.title.x = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
        axis.line.y = element_line(size = 0.5), 
        axis.text.x = element_blank(),axis.ticks.x=element_blank(),axis.text.y = element_text(family="Arial", face="plain", color="black", size=8, angle=0))
 
}

Compared baseline rate with non-parametric anova and bonferroni adjustment

kruskal.test(merged_df$`avg spike rate at baseline` ~ as.factor(merged_df$species))
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  merged_df$`avg spike rate at baseline` by as.factor(merged_df$species)
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 0.92956, df = 2, p-value = 0.6283
pairwise.wilcox.test(merged_df$`avg spike rate at baseline`, as.factor(merged_df$species), correct=FALSE, p.adjust.method = "bonferroni")
## 
##  Pairwise comparisons using Wilcoxon rank sum exact test 
## 
## data:  merged_df$`avg spike rate at baseline` and as.factor(merged_df$species) 
## 
##                  D. melanogaster D. subpulchrella
## D. subpulchrella 1.00            -               
## D. suzukii       1.00            0.89            
## 
## P value adjustment method: bonferroni
two_species <- rbind(merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. suzukii", ], merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. melanogaster", ])
two_new_species <- rbind(merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. subpulchrella", ], merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. melanogaster", ])
two_newer_species <- rbind(merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. subpulchrella", ], merged_df[merged_df$species == "D. suzukii", ])


t.test(two_new_species$`avg spike rate at baseline`~as.factor(two_new_species$species),p.adjust = "bonferroni")
